The excitation dependent luminescence behavior of CG is illustrated in Fig. 8
                     a. With the increase of excitation wavelength, noticeable spectral redshift is observed, which can be ascribed to the multiple emissive states on the CQDs surfaces [40]. Photoluminescence spectra of multicolor emitting CQD-RE silica matrix is analyzed to explore the energy transfer mechanisms between CQDs and Tb3+. it can be inferred that upon addition of Tb3+ ions, the blue emitting CQD-SiO2 changes to near white emitting glasses under excitation of 370 nm (Fig. 9
                     ). Decrease in fluorescence intensity of CQD suggests possible energy transfer to Tb3+ ions. UV illuminated CG glasses were tuned from blue to the white point in the CIE chart due to the neighboring terbium ions in CT7. Particularly, from the captured photographs and corresponding color points, tuning of emission chromaticity from intense blue (0.1809, 0.1992) to near white (0.2201, 0.3106) domain was observed.
